title: Sports Roundup: CHS and CCS volleyba;;; CBC soccer
text:
Sports Roundup: CHS and CCS volleyba;;; CBC soccer Posted: October 14, 2015 - 6:10pm By David McCollum LOG CABIN STAFF WRITER 
Conway’s volleyball team claimed victory No. 25 of the season Tuesday with a 25-16, 25-14, 25-8 victory over Van Buren. 
Aly Brinkley had 13 kills for the Lady Cats (25-5 10-3). McKenzie Hart added 16 assists. Sydney Trickett had three aces, Tori Popham, nine digs, and Bre Wells, three blocks., 
The Lady Cats (13-1, 11-0) won the JV match, 25-15, 25-11. Kylee French and Ashanti Davis had three kills each. Aryn Bumenberg had six assists. Blumenberg and Marlee Scaife had three aces each. Megan Solberg had five digs. CCS VOLLEYBALL 
Conway Christian’s volleyball team closed the regular season Tuesday night with their third straight victory. 
The Lady Eagles defeated first-place Atkins, 19-25, 25-23, 22-25, 26-24, 15-13. CBC SOCCER 
Lindenwood-Belleville (Illinois) defeated Central Baptist College, 2-0, in men’s soccer Tuesday. 
Oriol Lopez scored the only goal at 23:49 of the first quarter. 
CBC had one shot on goal. Bryce Deaton had five saves for the Mustangs.
